FBIS3-4143 "drchi059_a_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Mar 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General DPRK Ready To `Take Appropriate Steps' Against U.S. OW2803004894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0005 GMT 28 Mar 94 OW2803004894 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Luanda, March 27 (XINHUA) -- Pak Myong-ku, deputy foreign minister of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), said here today that his country will not yield to the pressure from the United States. Pak Myong-ku said this on his arrival at the Luanda inter-national airport. He has come here to pay a five-day visit to Angola. If the United States exerts pressure on his country by force of arms, the DPRK will "take appropriate steps," he said. He said, "We are ready politically and militarily to deal with the United States on our own, and the Americans should know this." Pak Myong-ku said his visit to the southern African country will "promote the bilateral relations between the two countries."
